description: a(n) = smallest number which is not the sum of exactly 1 or a(n-1) earlier terms.
example: a(5)=14 since all earlier numbers are either in list (1,2,3,5) or the sum of 3 terms from list (4=1+1+2, 6=2+2+2, ..., 12=2+5+5, 13=3+5+5).
author: _Erich Friedman_
extensions: More terms from _Henry Bottomley_, May 19 2000; and from Larry Reeves (larryr(AT)acm.org), May 08 2001
